Sentencas: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) have many advantages like low materials cost, excellent structural stability and high tolerance toward rapid thermal cycling over the traditional all ceramic SOFCs.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: To facilitate the commercialization of SOFCs, an all symmetrical MS-SOFC with the structure of Ce0.8Sm0.2O2-delta (SDC)-430L anode/Zr0.88Sc0.22Ce0.01O2.12(SSZ) electrolyte/SDC-430L cathode was developed by a tape casting-sintering-infiltration method.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: When measured in humidified hydrogen fuel and air oxidant, the maximum power densities (MPD) of the fuel cell are 220, 250 and 280 mW/cm(2) at 600, 650 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectra measurement shows that the cell performances are primarily dominated by polarization resistances derived from the SDC-430L electrodes.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The pure ohmic resistances are 0.16, 0.21 and 0.29 Omega.cm(2) and the polarization resistances are 0.67, 0.90 and 1.22 Omega.cm(2) at 700, 650 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Compared with that of the anode, polarization resistance of cathode is much higher.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: When measured at 650 degrees C, polarization resistances of the symmetrical SDC-430L cell are 0.23 and 1.92 Omega.cm(2) in 3% H2O-97% H-2 and air, respectively.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Further optimizing the cell structure (e.g., applying a finer 430L backbone) and the catalyst materials (e.g., Ag, Pt containing composite materials) may enhance the electrochemical performances of such MS-SOFC.
Titulo: All Symmetrical Metal Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
